<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-163-122  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 163 122.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 8 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CCA supplies SNA 4GL for IBM Enterprise System/9370. (ComputerCorporation of America) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Corporation of America (product introduction).andO;Product:   Horizon (Program development software) (product introduction)IBM Enterprise System-9370 (Minicomputer) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionFourth-Generation LanguagesSNA.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CCA SUPPLIES SNA 4GL FOR IBM ENTERPRISE SYSTEM/9370 CAMBRIDGE, MASSACHUSETTS,U.S.A., 1990 FEB 7 (NB) -- Computer Corporation of America has announced thattheir Horizon 4GL (fourth generation language) will now be available on IBM'sEnterprise System/9370 Models 10, 12 and 14.andM;As a fully functional 4GL with embedded SNA or Systems Network ArchitectureLogical Unit 6.2 (LU 6.2) communications protocols, Horizon is one of thefirst languages to run on the new 9370 platforms which lets users initiatecooperative processing between this system and DEC VAX, Wang, Unisys and allother SNA LU 6.2 compatible systems.andM;SNA is IBM's architecture which is intended to let various computer systems'programs interact and is a powerful feature of the OS/2 operating system.andP;  Asmore computer systems and languages provide for SNA, it becomes easier foroffices to integrate software running on a wide variety of platforms frommicrocomputers to mainframes.andM;(John McCormick/1990207/Press Contact: Lisa D. Gibson, Computer Corporationof America, 617-492-8860)</TEXT></DOC>